            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "I personally agree that special-casing local plugins feels a bit too much. The reasons for doing so seems to be to enable easier local plugin development:\n- Not having to `git init` in plugin's directory.\n- If it is a Git repo, not having to commit new changes and `vim.pack.update({ 'plugin1' }, { force = true })` each time.\n\nBoth of these cases are resolved by putting plugins in the '\\~/.local/share/nvim/site/pack/mine/{start,opt}/plugin1' or '\\~/.config/nvim/pack/mine/{start,opt}/plugin1'.\n\nThe idea was brought up by @lewis6991 and @clason, so maybe they can give more details.",
